cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper deals with lung nodule classification using deep neural networks and hyperparameter optimization. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of Bayesian optimization and Gaussian processes for hyperparameter optimization suggests the paper may also belong to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the proposed non-stationary kernel for the surrogate model and the use of evolutionary strategy may also relate to statistical learning (cs.SI) sub-category.
